enhanced_by.reason: The hasNext() method is used to determine if there is a next element, which is a prerequisite for the next() method.
The constructor initializes the iterators that the next() method will iterate over.
The remove() method operates on the last returned element, which is set by the next() method.
The next() method in ZippingIterator behaves similarly to the next() method in the standard Iterator interface, returning the next element.
